# Hotwire Standards

Follow the canonical standard: **`.ai/standards/hotwire.md`**

Key rules:
- Hotwire for server-rendered apps with light interactivity; React/Inertia for complex client state
- Turbo Frames scope partial updates; give frames stable `id`s
- Authorize Turbo Stream subscriptions per user; keep payloads small
- One Stimulus controller per behavior; use `data-*` actions/targets/values, no inline JS
- Server remains source of truth — no duplicated business logic in Stimulus
- Preserve focus across Turbo updates; respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

